file.name: openapi.yml
file.content:
openapi: "3.0.0"
info:
  version: 0.1.0
  title: GitLab Clippy
  license:
    name: MIT
servers:
  - url: https://gitlab-cq-rust.herokuapp.com
    description: Production server
  - url: https://gitlab-cq-rust-staging.herokuapp.com
    description: Staging server
  - url: http://localhost:3000
    description: Local server
paths:
  /clippy:
    post:
      summary: "Upload the clippy output and receive the GitLab code quality report"
      requestBody:
        content:
          text/plain:
            schema:
              type: string
              format: binary
      responses:
        '200':
          description: GitLab code quality report
          content:
            application/json:
              schema:
                $ref: '#/components/schemas/ArrayOfCQReport'
        '400':
          description: Failed to parse the output
          content:
            application/json:
              schema:
                $ref: "#/components/schemas/Error"

components:
  schemas:
    ArrayOfCQReport:
      type: array
      items:
        $ref: '#/components/schemas/CQReport'
    CQReport:
      type: object
      required:
        - description
        - fingerprint
        - lines
      properties:
        description:
          type: string
          example: you seem to be trying to use match for destructuring a single pattern. Consider using `if let`
        fingerprint:
          type: string
          example: 86ffc66e391a1594d07b5b1ccae7d35e
        location:
          type: object
          required:
            - path
            - lines
          properties:
            path:
              type: string
              example: src/main.rs
            lines:
              type: object
              required:
                - begin
              properties:
                begin:
                  type: integer
                  format: int32
                  example: 35
    Error:
      type: object
      required:
        - message
        - description
      properties:
        message:
          type: string
          example: Unable to parse body
        description:
          type: string
          example: stream did not contain valid UTF-8
